                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I was hoping that some of my fellow enchanters would be able to offer me some insight into how to help my group succeed on Hard Adventures in LDoN.
<br />
My regular group consists of: 65 beastlord, 65 cleric, 65 enchanter (me), 65 necromancer, 65 warrior and either a 65 shaman or a 63 shadow knight.  As a group we have always pushed ourselves; and this week  decided that the next way to step up our game a bit was to try hard adventures.  So far in our attempts, we have been on track for winning until i have to pacify (and even mez in some cases).  I知 getting about an 80% resist rate on pacify, with somewhat better luck with mez.  Either way the resists are frequent enough on both, that i'm being quickly killed because of them, which releases my charmed pet along with the rest of the adds onto my group, and we end up wiping (those of us who can稚 FD, anyway ).  While we池e not uber, we are decently equipped; and I知 fairly certain that I知 the one causing us to lose.
<br />
These adventures have convinced me to get to LR5 as fast as i can, so i at least get hit less when I知 resisted.  But I知 curious as to what else i can do.   I'm incredibly frustrated feeling like i'm the weak link in my group.  
<br />
Those of you who succeed on these, what are your strategies etc for winning?  Any advice is greatly appreciated.  Thank you in advance <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
illumine</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=741724" target="_blank" class="postlink"> illumine Nauti </a>
