                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">a grp of 65's -- ench/war/shmn/dru/cleric/some dps class (wiz/rogue/sk etc) is prolly the most well balanced group for hard.  Granted most of these chars are wearing either full elemental or better, but if you really want to know how to beat hards withoutmuch difficulty it's this system of backups.
<br />

<br />
i mean, in the case of bad pulls, i can mez and not have to freak because mobs hitting for 900+ are going rampant, the shaman is covering that.  Or if the clr dies, the dru/shmn can backup heal.  Hard really isnt worth it tho.  You can do 2 easy adv's just as fast for about the same ap.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=607836" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.tech-unleashed.com/images/kellsig2.gif" border="0" /></a>~Coercer of <a href="http://www.waster.net/wudan" target="_blank" class="postlink">Wudan</a>~
