                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I think Hard Adventures are great.  There are a ton of ways to pull but I do not recommend pacification with the resist rates for it in LDON.  Pulling with root or mez works fine almost all of the time, but generally I would leave that for one of the melee to handle.  Its much easier to mez a few quickly when their primary aggro was on a different puller.  Have your shaman help root one of the few that are incoming so that you have one less to worry about, then mez/debuff it once the others are handled.  It also sounds like you have 1-2 people that can FD in your normal group layout so that adds a lot of possibilities.
<br />

<br />
When I am playing with my regular group a lot of the times I send the pet in first to tank a few, then I just mez targets off of him.  If you don't get a resist you can sit there mezzing off the 3-4 the pet may be tanking with ease.  If you get a resist your group members can chose the first one that charges you as their primary target, then continue to mez things off pet.  Most of the problems I can imagine in other peoples hard adventure groups is not knowing how to back the enchanter up when it comes to charming.  If you have a paladin/cleric that is on the ball with back up stuns, everything usually runs perfectly.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=219984&resize=true" target="_blank" class="postlink">Nautimus Miamivice</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.legacyofsteel.net/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Legacy of Steel</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
