                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">One big difference in hard adv's vs normal is that the entire group needs to become the crowd controller and support for your charmed pet.  If we get a 3-4 pull the druid and shaman are rooting and the shm is using her knockback-stun aa while I mez.  If I get a charm break the cleric is stunning my pet with me and the shm is re-maloing.  If my pet breaks on a multi-pull the warr ae taunts or the sk gets quick agro to pull the heat off me for recharming.  Everyone in the group has to be aware of everything everyone else is doing and be able to assist in their own way.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
