                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Charm is they key to winning hard every time, quickly.  You don't need time gear, either. I do this perfectly well Velious equipped.  Here is what to do:
<br />

<br />
1. Fight in a big room, and stand FAR from your pet.  Make someone pull to the pet.  Don't sweat multiple incs up to 5. 
<br />

<br />
2. Maximize your pet's melee damage output with haste and two weapons.
<br />

<br />
3. Park pet where it will intercept incoming pulls.  Make it tank until they are mezzed.  Don't worry about it's health. It will live through 4 pulls easily, usually killing 2 of them in the time it takes to mez two.
<br />

<br />
4. Have 63+ cleric or paladin ready to stun pet the instant it breaks.  Tash if needed, recharm, send it back in.  If charm is resisted, run around the big room like a deer until it the pet is stunned again.  Spirit of wolf helps, but it's not a necessity.
<br />

<br />
5. This is the hard part--convince the rest of the party to NEVER engage your pet in combat, taunt it off you, or do ANYTHING to it except stun or malo it so you can recharm.  As long as it's chasing you, it's no danger to them.  If it's on one of them, it will squish them.  The tank's job during charm breaks is to handle adds while you do pet control. 
<br />

<br />
I've never lost a hard adventure with these tactics.  I've been squished twice in around 20 adventures</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
