                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Did quite a few Hard Crawls over this past weekend, never charmed we won more than we lost, really nice loot.  Pretty much everyone I had spoken to stated that you need a Bard puller.  Our groups used a monk puller.  You can win without a charmed pet, regardless one wipeout usually means you fail.  The failures we had was with 1 full/near wipeout (near being Cleric or me (enc)) and we were within 1 or 2 drops from winning.
<br />

<br />
Collections are really the way to go on these missions in my opinion or a low Slaughter.
<br />

<br />
All I have to say is after doing all the hard crawls we did and then doing a normal one, it was boring.  I have LR5, ID5, Chanelling Focus 3, and I was able to off tank slowed mobs with Arcane Rune.  You can relax ALOT more on normal missions than hard.  Really no one can go afk during a hard.  You need all the time you can get.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
